;; kami.sim/defsystem is a custom def-like macro
;; ((name opts-map [world dt] & body)) that clj-kondo doesn't know about,
;; so it can't see that `name`/`world`/`dt` are being *defined*/*bound* and
;; flags them as unresolved symbols. def-catch-all tells clj-kondo to treat
;; the whole form loosely like a def, without needing an exact shape match.
{:lint-as {kami.sim/defsystem clj-kondo.lint-as/def-catch-all}}
